01:23:25,680 --> 01:23:27,159
I want it. If I didn't want it,

1252
01:23:27,241 --> 01:23:29,280
I wouldn't have let you
take the car out this morning.

1253
01:23:29,360 --> 01:23:31,559
I made you take the car this morning.

1254
01:23:31,641 --> 01:23:33,199
I could've stopped you.

1255
01:23:33,360 --> 01:23:36,280
It is possible to stop
Mr. Ferris Bueller, you know?

1256
01:23:36,360 --> 01:23:39,160
No, I want it. I'm gonna take it. That's it.

1257
01:23:40,240 --> 01:23:42,480
When Morris comes home,

1258
01:23:43,441 --> 01:23:45,640
he and I'll just have a little chat.

1259
01:23:47,440 --> 01:23:48,599
It's cool.

1260
01:23:49,400 --> 01:23:51,279
No, it's gonna be good.

1261
01:23:52,800 --> 01:23:54,240
Thanks anyway.

1262
01:24:02,960 --> 01:24:04,319
This is a shock to me.

1263
01:24:04,401 --> 01:24:06,880
I mean, first of all, I don't know
why she wasn't in school.

1264
01:24:06,960 --> 01:24:09,040
And second of all, I just can't believe

1265
01:24:09,120 --> 01:24:11,520
she came to you
with this story about an intruder.

1266
01:24:11,600 --> 01:24:15,520
Well, for whatever reason she did it,
I think she's had a pretty good scare.

1267
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:18,400
Well, I really appreciate your calling me.
Really.

1268
01:24:18,480 --> 01:24:20,359
I can assure you that her father
and I are going

1269
01:24:20,441 --> 01:24:22,400
to have a long talk
with her when we get home.

1270
01:24:22,480 --> 01:24:23,799
Thank you so much.

1271
01:24:24,961 --> 01:24:27,679
Oh, by the way,
I hope your son is feeling better.

1272
01:24:27,841 --> 01:24:29,039
I beg your pardon?

1273
01:24:29,121 --> 01:24:31,919
Tell him all the guys
at the station here are pulling for him.

1274
01:24:32,880 --> 01:24:33,880
Oh, right.

1275
01:24:38,401 --> 01:24:39,959
(CLEARING THROAT)

1276
01:24:41,561 --> 01:24:42,920
(JEANIE CHUCKLES)

1277
01:24:43,000 --> 01:24:45,359
- Hi.
- Don't "hi" me, young lady.

1278
01:24:45,841 --> 01:24:47,559
- I wanna get out of here, now, all right?
- Okay.

1279
01:24:47,640 --> 01:24:49,159
No, now. Let's get out of here.

1280
01:24:49,241 --> 01:24:50,839
- Okay.
- Okay?

1281
01:24:50,921 --> 01:24:51,880
- Yes.
- Now.

1282
01:24:51,960 --> 01:24:52,919
Fine.

1283
01:24:53,440 --> 01:24:54,399
Okay.

1284
01:24:59,320 --> 01:25:02,479
- She's a little hyper.
- Yeah.

1285
01:25:05,200 --> 01:25:09,199
Let's not ruin this
with a lot of talk, all right? Okay?

1286
01:25:10,440 --> 01:25:12,479
You didn't tell me your name.

1287
01:25:13,521 --> 01:25:18,080
Well, it's Jean,
but, a lot of guys call me Shauna.

1288
01:25:19,120 --> 01:25:20,400
Okay, Jean.

1289
01:25:20,961 --> 01:25:21,920
Cool.

1290
01:25:23,200 --> 01:25:24,559
That's great.

1291
01:25:25,601 --> 01:25:27,159
I'll see you, okay?

1292
01:25:28,320 --> 01:25:29,280
Yeah.

1293
01:25:29,601 --> 01:25:30,960
(LAUGHING)

1294
01:25:32,400 --> 01:25:34,159
KATIE: Jeanie, now!

1295
01:25:34,880 --> 01:25:38,119
- Now!
- Okay!

1296
01:25:39,161 --> 01:25:41,199
(JEANIE SINGING DANKE SCHOEN)

1297
01:25:45,720 --> 01:25:47,400
I had a great time today.

1298
01:25:48,280 --> 01:25:50,680
Yeah. It was pretty cool.

1299
01:25:53,041 --> 01:25:55,399
Do you...
Do you think Cameron's gonna be okay?

1300
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:56,480
Oh, yeah.

1301
01:25:57,200 --> 01:25:59,600
Yeah, sure. For the first time in his life.

1302
01:25:59,881 --> 01:26:01,520
He's gonna be just fine.

1303
01:26:01,840 --> 01:26:03,919
(THE EDGE OF FOREVER PLAYING)

1304
01:26:09,680 --> 01:26:12,879
You knew what you were doing when
you woke up this morning, didn't you?

1305
01:26:13,520 --> 01:26:15,920
Me? No.

1306
01:26:34,640 --> 01:26:38,239
Oh, shit. I have to go.

1307
01:26:40,201 --> 01:26:42,079
- I'll call you tonight.
- Okay.

1308
01:26:46,121 --> 01:26:48,560
- I love you!
- I love you, too!

1309
01:26:50,480 --> 01:26:52,079
He's gonna marry me.

1310
01:26:55,760 --> 01:26:58,279
KATIE: Do you know what it's like
to be pulled out of work

1311
01:26:58,360 --> 01:27:00,679
to pick up your daughter
at the police station?

1312
01:27:00,760 --> 01:27:01,760
JEANIE: No, not really.

1313
01:27:01,840 --> 01:27:03,279
Well, on top of everything else,

1314
01:27:03,360 --> 01:27:06,599
I was about to close the damn deal
with the Vermont people.

1315
01:27:06,800 --> 01:27:08,159
I'm sorry.

1316
01:27:10,440 --> 01:27:12,639
I was gonna take my commission
and buy Ferris a car.

1317
01:27:12,721 --> 01:27:13,879
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1318
01:27:13,961 --> 01:27:14,920
(KATIE SCREAMS)

1319
01:27:15,000 --> 01:27:18,839
KATIE: Jeanie, what the hell
are you doing? You trying to kill us?

1320
01:27:19,041 --> 01:27:20,479
God, look at this mess.

1321
01:27:20,560 --> 01:27:23,359
Paper all over the place.
I'll never get this back in order.

1322
01:27:23,440 --> 01:27:25,039
(KATIE SCREAMING)

1323
01:27:31,000 --> 01:27:32,480
Jeanie!

1324
01:27:41,080 --> 01:27:44,519
- Slow down! Now! Now!
- I can't drive when you're yelling at me!

1325
01:27:44,681 --> 01:27:45,640
Stop it!

1326
01:27:48,760 --> 01:27:50,319
(SIRENS BLARING)

1327
01:28:15,160 --> 01:28:16,879
- Hi, how you doing? Ferris Bueller.
- Hi.

1328
01:28:31,160 --> 01:28:32,599
(HORN BLARING)

1329
01:29:04,680 --> 01:29:06,000
(INAUDIBLE)

1330
01:29:41,520 --> 01:29:43,040
- FERRIS: No, don't get up.
- Hey.

1331
01:29:43,120 --> 01:29:44,559
FERRIS: Smells delicious.

1332
01:29:45,360 --> 01:29:46,880
- Dinner's ready.
- GIRL: What?

1333
01:29:47,080 --> 01:29:48,399
Who's that?

1334
01:30:20,200 --> 01:30:23,559
- What's wrong?
- Everything.

1335
01:30:23,920 --> 01:30:26,439
I just picked up Jeanie
at the police station.

1336
01:30:28,400 --> 01:30:30,559
She got a speeding ticket,
another speeding ticket

1337
01:30:30,640 --> 01:30:32,359
and I lost the Vermont deal
because of her.

1338
01:30:32,440 --> 01:30:34,199
(SIGHING) I think we should shoot her.

1339
01:30:40,720 --> 01:30:42,319
Looking for this?

1340
01:30:54,480 --> 01:30:55,799
I got you, Ferris.

1341
01:30:56,200 --> 01:30:58,319
- How's Ferris? Let's go check on him.
- Okay, honey. Yeah.

1342
01:30:59,160 --> 01:31:00,479
KATIE: How was your day?

1343
01:31:01,480 --> 01:31:03,999
ROONEY: I have dreamed about this.

1344
01:31:05,040 --> 01:31:08,999
This time, goddamn, you little bastard,

1345
01:31:09,920 --> 01:31:12,039
I've got you right where I want you.

1346
01:31:12,280 --> 01:31:13,879
Ferris, we're home.

1347
01:31:16,040 --> 01:31:16,999
ROONEY: So,

1348
01:31:18,960 --> 01:31:22,239
how would you feel
about another year of high school?

1349
01:31:23,640 --> 01:31:27,279
Under my close personal supervision.

1350
01:31:28,960 --> 01:31:29,919
Hi.

1351
01:31:32,360 --> 01:31:36,079
Thank God you're all right. You know,
we've been worried sick about you.

1352
01:31:40,840 --> 01:31:43,199
Thank you, Mr. Rooney,
for driving him home.

1353
01:31:43,760 --> 01:31:47,719
Now I want you to go upstairs
and get in bed.

1354
01:31:54,800 --> 01:31:56,679
(FERRIS CLEARING THROAT)

1355
01:31:58,440 --> 01:31:59,639
Scoot!

1356
01:32:01,200 --> 01:32:02,879
Can you imagine
someone as sick as Ferris

1357
01:32:02,960 --> 01:32:05,159
trying to walk home from the hospital?

1358
01:32:06,600 --> 01:32:07,999
Oh, kids.

1359
01:32:11,000 --> 01:32:14,839
By the way, Mr. Rooney,
you left your wallet on the kitchen floor.

1360
01:32:16,440 --> 01:32:17,639
(GASPS)

1361
01:32:19,480 --> 01:32:20,799
(SPLASHING)

1362
01:32:23,080 --> 01:32:24,559
(DOG GROWLING)

1363
01:32:27,200 --> 01:32:28,799
(ROONEY SCREAMING)

1364
01:32:28,880 --> 01:32:29,919
(DOG GROWLING)

1365
01:32:52,400 --> 01:32:53,679
(SNORING)

1366
01:33:18,320 --> 01:33:19,279
Honey.

1367
01:33:20,880 --> 01:33:23,759
- He's still awfully warm.
- TOM: How do you feel?

1368
01:33:25,040 --> 01:33:28,079
150% better. Thank you.

1369
01:33:29,840 --> 01:33:30,799
Please,

1370
01:33:31,000 --> 01:33:34,319
don't make me stay home again.
I wanna go to school.

1371
01:33:35,040 --> 01:33:39,119
(STUTTERING) I have to graduate
in June. And I want...

1372
01:33:39,680 --> 01:33:41,079
TOM: Ferris, you're sick.

1373
01:33:41,560 --> 01:33:43,999
Now don't go pushing it
and making yourself worse.

1374
01:33:45,080 --> 01:33:47,759
- Maybe you're right, Dad.
- I know I'm right, pal.

1375
01:33:49,560 --> 01:33:51,759
How'd you get to be so sweet?

1376
01:33:52,200 --> 01:33:54,319
Years of practice.

1377
01:34:02,640 --> 01:34:04,038
(KATIE SIGHS)

1378
01:34:04,240 --> 01:34:05,359
Blanket.

1379
01:34:15,120 --> 01:34:16,159
Get well.

1380
01:34:16,239 --> 01:34:17,439
(GROWLS)

1381
01:34:18,000 --> 01:34:19,359
Come on.

1382
01:34:21,999 --> 01:34:25,879
Listen, I'm going to get myself settled
and I'll bring a hot cup of soup, okay?

1383
01:34:25,960 --> 01:34:27,279
(EXCLAIMING)

1384
01:34:33,640 --> 01:34:34,799
(SIGHS)

1385
01:34:36,240 --> 01:34:37,199
Yup.

1386
01:34:37,720 --> 01:34:39,919
I said it before and I'll say it again.

1387
01:34:40,400 --> 01:34:42,119
Life moves pretty fast.

1388
01:34:42,520 --> 01:34:46,079
If you don't stop and look around
once in a while, you could miss it.

1389
01:34:46,160 --> 01:34:47,719
(OH YEAH PLAYING)

1390
01:34:56,720 --> 01:34:59,239
ROONEY: Four years of chasing this kid.

1391
01:35:00,040 --> 01:35:03,278
Four years he has been
making a fool of me.

1392
01:35:13,360 --> 01:35:17,039
Hey, Mr. Rooney, what's going on?

1393
01:35:19,759 --> 01:35:21,999
Did you get in a fight?

1394
01:35:23,400 --> 01:35:24,559
Want a lift?

1395
01:37:06,319 --> 01:37:09,679
I bet you never smelled
a real school bus before.

1396
01:37:23,080 --> 01:37:24,158
Gummy Bear?

1397
01:37:25,720 --> 01:37:28,798
They've been in my pocket.
They're real warm and soft.

1398
01:38:14,840 --> 01:38:16,278
You're still here?

1399
01:38:18,999 --> 01:38:20,159
It's over.

1400
01:38:22,120 --> 01:38:23,238
Go home.

1401
01:38:27,560 --> 01:38:28,519
Go.

